    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Next repeat the process with the new branches. Since 2 x 3 = 6 and 5 x 2 = 10, I‚Äôll write the factors underneath their respective branches. When I come to a <strong>prime number </strong>‚Äî<strong> </strong>a number whose only factors is 1 and itself ‚Äî I circle it indicating that the branch is finished.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
